    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="248"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d248">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1229.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 31.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 13, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department encloses herewith three forms<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d248fn3">Not printed.</note> marked 1, 2 and 3. Immediately
                    after the Dominican Congress shall have formally authorized the President of the
                    Dominican Republic to negotiate bonds now in the depository account with the
                    Guaranty Trust Company of New York to produce approximately $1,600,000 for
                    certain purposes, orders corresponding to these forms should be executed by the
                    Minister of Finance and forwarded by you to the Department. When approved by the
                    Department and forwarded to the Guaranty Trust Company the effect of the orders
                    as per forms 1 and 2 will be to convert bonds into cash to the extent of
                    approximately $1,600,000. The order as per form No. 3 will result in
                    transferring from the depository account $1,600,000 of cash to the credit of an
                    account entitled “Dominican Government Special Account” subject to disbursement
                    on drafts of the Minister of Finance to be approved by the <hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >Department of State</hi> under such regulations as may hereafter be
                    determined and prescribed.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. B. Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
